    "Now we can think about defining our prior and likelihood to be used in the MCMC.\n",

    "trainX = np.load(cache_dir+\"class_aemulus/train/X_sigma-v3.npy\")\n",
    "mvn = multivariate_normal(trainX.mean(axis=0), np.cov(trainX, rowvar=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "def log_prior(theta):\n",
    "    return mvn.logpdf(theta[:,:])"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next we define a Gaussian likelihood with the form $$\\ln{\\mathcal{L}(d|\\theta)}=-\\frac{1}{2}\\frac{(P-P'(\\theta))^2}{\\sigma^2}.$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $P$ is our `power_true`, $P'(\\theta)$ is the emulator prediction for the parameters $\\theta$, and $\\sigma$ is our `noise`. We construct this function such that it expects multiple parameter sets to evaluate, exploiting the batch prediction speed from `Matryoshka`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def log_like(theta, obs_pow, noise):\n",
    "    preds_T = TransferEmu.emu_predict(theta[:,[0,1,3,5,6]], mean_or_full='mean')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    preds_power = interp1d(TransferEmu.kbins, MatryHM.power0_v2(TransferEmu.kbins, preds_T, sigma8=theta[:,2],\n",
    "                                                                ns=theta[:,4]))(k_obs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    res = obs_pow - preds_power\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return -0.5*np.sum(res**2/noise**2, axis=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The final function we need before runnig our MCMC combines the log-likelihood and the log-prior to calculate the log-probability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def log_prob(theta, obs_pow, noise):\n",
    "    theta = np.array(theta)\n",
    "    lp = log_prior(theta)\n",
    "    ll = log_like(theta, obs_pow, noise)\n",
    "    return ll+lp\n",
    "\n",
    "# We also define a function for the negative log_prob, this will be used with the minimize function from scipy so\n",
    "# does not exploit batch predictions.\n",
    "def neg_log_prob(theta, obs_pow, icov):\n",
    "    theta = theta.reshape(1, -1)\n",
    "    return -(log_prob(theta, obs_pow, icov))"
   ]
